Exo Dialect: Which Ops Are Necessary?

3 of 8 can be trivially replaced. 5 of 8 are structurally necessary.


CAN BE ELIMINATED
=================

exo.instr -> func.call (no results)
  Opaque call by symbol name, no return value. Semantically identical to func.call.
  - main.py:342: InstrOp(name, args) -> CallOp(name, args, [])
  - inline_avx2.py, inline_blas.py: change pattern match from exo.InstrOp to func.CallOp
    (all patterns already guard on callee name, both ops have same callee/arguments attrs)

exo.extern -> func.call (with result)
  Same as instr but with a return value.
  - main.py:245: ExternOp(name, args, type) -> CallOp(name, args, [type])
  - inline_blas.py:59 ConvertSelect: change type annotation, op.result -> op.res[0]

exo.reduce -> inline expansion
  Compound op (load + add + store). Expand into exo.read + arith.add + exo.assign at IR gen time.
  - main.py:265-273: emit ReadOp + arith add + AssignOp instead of ReduceOp
  - delete ConvertReduceOp from convert_memref_to_llvm.py:153-205
  - delete ConvertReduceToTensor from convert_scalar_ref.py:71-83
  - delete ConvertReduceOp from convert_tensor_ref.py:60-108
  - convert_scalar_ref.py:94: ReduceOp check becomes AssignOp-only
  - CSE already eliminates the duplicate GEP from separate read+assign


NECESSARY (tied to manual-stride lowering)
==========================================

These exist because the project uses raw pointers + manual stride computation
instead of memref descriptors + standard MLIR lowering. Replacing any of them
requires switching the entire lowering strategy.

exo.alloc    - custom memory space allocation (DRAM->malloc, VEC_AVX2->alloca)
exo.read     - gep + llvm.load with manual stride math (carries explicit sizes)
exo.assign   - gep + llvm.store with manual stride math (carries explicit sizes)
exo.window   - gep + cast for sub-views (explicit input/output sizes)
exo.interval - helper for window index computation, erased after window lowering


